<div id="about-the-community" class="section-spacer">
    <h2 class="sect-title">About Elbow Park</h2>
    <div class="col-grid-2">
        <div>
            <p class="par-lg">Elbow Park resides in an elegant community lining the banks of the Elbow River with its
                heritage homes. Established during Calgary’s growth prior to the First World War, Elbow Park once
                huddled in the shadow of Mount Royal homes, but has now prospered as an upper class neighbourhood and
                one of Calgary’s best communities. </p>
            <p class="par-xl">In 2010, Avenue Magazine ranked Elbow Park as the #5 best community in Calgary based on a
                citywide survey.</p>
            <p class="par-lg">Calgary's old money district, Elbow Park-Glencoe is located on the eastern banks of Elbow
                River. 14 street is to the southwest, while the southern neighborhood consists of Britannia and the
                River Park. The Earl Grey Park forms the northern border of Elbow Park-Glencoe community. Believed to be
                one of the oldest communities in Calgary, Elbow Park-Glencoe lives up to its rich past with its scenic
                tree-lined winding pathways.</p>

        </div>
